'''Antonee “Jedi” Robinson''' (born August 8, 1997) is a professional [[soccer]] player who plays as a [[left-back]] for {{English football updater|Fulham}} club [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham.]] Born in England, he represents the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States national team]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Antonee Robinson Fulham Defender, Profile & Stats {{!}} Premier League |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/players/169528/antonee-robinson/overview |access-date=August 23, 2025 |website=www.premierleague.com |language=en}}</ref>

Previously a youth player with [[Everton F.C.|Everton]], he went on loan spells to several [[EFL Championship]] clubs until signing with [[Premier League]] club [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] in 2020 for £2 million.<ref name=":0" /> Following relegation after his first season, he won the [[2021–22 EFL Championship]] and was listed on the [[2021–22 EFL Championship#Annual|2021–22 Team of the Season]].<ref name=":1" /> He won the [[2023–24 Fulham F.C. season|2023–24]] Fulham Player of the Season award, and is considered one of the Premier League's best full-backs.<ref name=":2">{{Cite news |last=Rutzler |first=Peter |title=Fulham's player of the season – Antonee Robinson |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5507552/2024/05/23/robinson-fulham-usmnt-poty/ |access-date=May 24, 2024 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref name=":3">{{Cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RHhoVoR9r88 |title=Cole Palmer, Antonee Robinson in Data Team of the Season {{!}} Generation xG {{!}} NBC Sports |date=May 22, 2024 |last=NBC Sports |access-date=May 24, 2024 |via=YouTube}}</ref><ref name=":6">{{Cite web |date=November 13, 2022 |title=The 25 best left backs in world football – ranked |url=https://www.90min.com/posts/the-25-best-left-backs-in-world-football-ranked |access-date=July 9, 2024 |website=90min.com |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref name=":7">{{Cite news |last1=Rueter |first1=Jeff |last2=Jones |first2=Andy |title=How Antonee Robinson became the best left-back in the Premier League |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6013281/2024/12/26/antonee-robinson-premier-league-left-back-best/?source=twitteruk&utm_campaign=twitterfc&utm_medium=social |access-date=December 27, 2024 |work=The New York Times |date=December 26, 2024 |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>

Robinson represented the United States across several youth levels and made his debut for the [[United States men's national soccer team|senior team]] in May 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Antonee Robinson {{!}} USMNT {{!}} U.S. Soccer Official Site |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/players/r/antonee-robinson |access-date=December 15, 2024 |website=www.ussoccer.com |language=en}}</ref> He won the [[U.S. Soccer Player of the Year|U.S. Player of the Year]] award for 2024.<ref name=":8">{{Cite web |date=January 5, 2025 |title=Antonee Robinson surprised with U.S. Soccer Male Player of the Year award by Tim Howard (video) |url=https://www.nbcsports.com/soccer/news/antonee-robinson-surprised-with-u-s-soccer-male-player-of-the-year-award-by-tim-howard-video |access-date=January 5, 2025 |website=NBC Sports |language=en-US}}</ref>

==Early life==
Antonee Robinson was born in [[Milton Keynes]], [[England]] on August 8, 1997, to father Marlon, who had emigrated to the United States, settling in [[White Plains, New York]], and later naturalizing as a [[Citizenship of the United States|US citizen]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Beatrice |first=Stephanie |date=December 10, 2023 |title=Antonee Robinson's parents, siblings, ethnicity, and background |url=https://soka54.com/players/antonee-robinson/ |access-date=September 6, 2025 |website=Soka54 |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Antonee Robinson {{!}} USMNT {{!}} U.S. Soccer Official Site |url=https://ussoccer.com/players/r/antonee-robinson |access-date=September 6, 2025 |website=ussoccer.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=July 30, 2017 |title=Get to Know MNT Defender Antonee Robinson |url=https://ussoccer.com/stories/2018/03/get-to-know-mnt-defender-antonee-robinson |access-date=September 6, 2025 |website=ussoccer.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=September 6, 2025 |title=Fulham fullback Antonee Robinson: Why I committed to USA |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/fulham-fullback-antonee-robinson-why-i-committed-to-usa-32669323 |access-date=September 6, 2025 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref> Robinson was raised in [[Liverpool]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-08 |title=Haaland, Bale, Musiala, Frimpong: Players who could have played for England... |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c4gx1xxg7x1o |access-date=2026-05-15 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

==Youth career==
Robinson came through Everton's [[Everton F.C. Reserves and Academy|academy]], having been with the academy since the age of 11.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.evertonfc.com/players/a/ar/antonee-robinson|title=Antonee Robinson|publisher=Everton Official Site|access-date=August 10, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170810170424/http://www.evertonfc.com/players/a/ar/antonee-robinson|archive-date=August 10, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> In June 2013, he signed a scholarship with the club, becoming a full-time player.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2013/06/29/14-become-scholars|title=14 Become Scholars|publisher=Everton F.C.|date=June 29, 2013|access-date=February 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180112194918/http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2013/06/29/14-become-scholars|archive-date=January 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Everton===
While with Everton's U18 side, Robinson suffered injuries that saw him sidelined most of the time. He appeared for the U21 side toward the end of the 2014–15 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2015/05/26/thorniley-wins-top-prize-at-academy-awards|title=Thorniley Takes Top Academy Prize|publisher=Everton F.C.|date=May 26, 2015|access-date=February 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150920085615/http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2015/05/26/thorniley-wins-top-prize-at-academy-awards|archive-date=September 20, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> As a result, he was awarded the club's Under-18 Players' Player of the Season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2015/06/05/robinson-pleased-with-recognition|title=Robinson Pleased With Recognition|publisher=Everton F.C.|date=June 5, 2015|access-date=February 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180214203032/http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2015/06/05/robinson-pleased-with-recognition|archive-date=February 14, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> At the end of the 2014–15 season, he signed his first professional contract with the club after being offered a new contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2015/06/10/club-submits-retained-list|title=Club Submits Retained List|publisher=Everton F.C.|date=June 10, 2015|access-date=February 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170825210345/http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2015/06/10/club-submits-retained-list|archive-date=August 25, 2017|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2015/07/03/grant-pens-new-deal|title=Grant Pens New Deal|publisher=Everton F.C.|date=July 3, 2015|access-date=February 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924040604/http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2015/07/03/grant-pens-new-deal|archive-date=September 24, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref>

However, Robinson spent most of the 2015–16 season sidelined by torn cartilage under his kneecap, resulting in knee surgery.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2016/05/29/next-generation-whos-next|title=Next Generation: Who's Next?|publisher=Everton F.C.|date=May 29, 2016|access-date=February 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170825212413/http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2016/05/29/next-generation-whos-next|archive-date=August 25, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Despite this, he signed a one-year contract extension on July 15, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2016/07/15/new-deals-for-charsley-and-robinson|title=Charsley & Robinson Extend Deals|publisher=Everton F.C.|date=July 15, 2016|access-date=February 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170825212604/http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2016/07/15/new-deals-for-charsley-and-robinson|archive-date=August 25, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Robinson then played all three matches in the [[EFL Trophy]], which saw [[Everton F.C. Reserves and Academy|Everton U23s]] eliminated in the Group stage. He also became a regular for the U23 side.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.evertonfc.com/fixtures/2010-to-2019/2016-2017/football-league-trophy/cheltenham-town|title=Robinson Targets Trophy Progress|publisher=Everton F.C.|date=October 4, 2016|access-date=February 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180214212355/http://www.evertonfc.com/fixtures/2010-to-2019/2016-2017/football-league-trophy/cheltenham-town|archive-date=February 14, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> At the end of the 2016–17 season, Robinson signed a two-year contract extension with the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2017/07/06/robinson-signs-contract-extension|title=New Deal For Young Blues Defender|publisher=Everton F.C.|date=July 6, 2017|access-date=February 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170709005741/http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2017/07/06/robinson-signs-contract-extension|archive-date=July 9, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>

====Loan to Bolton Wanderers====
On August 4, 2017, it was announced that Antonee Robinson had signed on loan with [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]] until January 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bwfc.co.uk/news/2017/august/wanderers-sign-premier-league-starlet-on-loan/|title=Wanderers sign Antonee Robinson on loan|publisher=Bolton Wanderers F.C.|date=August 4, 2017|access-date=February 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170805060157/https://www.bwfc.co.uk/news/2017/august/wanderers-sign-premier-league-starlet-on-loan/|archive-date=August 5, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>

Five days after joining the club, on August 9, 2017, he made his debut in a 2–1 [[EFL Cup|League Cup]] win at [[Crewe Alexandra F.C.|Crewe Alexandra]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Crewe Alexandra 1 – 2 Bolton Wanderers|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40798476|publisher=BBC Sport|date=August 9, 2017|access-date=February 14, 2018}}</ref> Two weeks later, on August 22, 2017, he set up a goal for [[Jem Karacan]] to score the club's third goal in a 3–2 win over [[Sheffield Wednesday F.C.|Sheffield Wednesday]] in the League Cup.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bolton Wanderers 3 – 2 Sheffield Wednesday|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40932011|publisher=BBC Sport|date=August 22, 2017|access-date=February 14, 2018}}</ref> He made his league debut for the side on September 9, 2017, in a 3–0 loss against [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]], playing the full 90 minutes.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bolton Wanderers 0 – 3 Middlesbrough|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/41132802|publisher=BBC Sport|date=September 9, 2017|access-date=February 14, 2018}}</ref> Robinson then established himself in the left-back position, beating out competition from [[Andrew Taylor (footballer, born 1986)|Andrew Taylor]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Dynamic Everton full-back Antonee Robinson can be out of this world for Bolton Wanderers, says Phil Parkinson|url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/sport/15636276.Dynamic_Everton_loanee_Robinson_can_be_out_of_this_world/|publisher=The Bolton News|date=November 5, 2017|access-date=February 14, 2018}}</ref> It was announced on January 5, 2018, that Robinson had agreed to stay at Bolton for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2018/01/05/robinson-bolton-loan-extended|title=Robinson's Bolton Loan Extended|publisher=Everton F.C.|date=January 5, 2018|access-date=February 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180108174846/http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2018/01/05/robinson-bolton-loan-extended|archive-date=January 8, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===Wigan Athletic===
On July 15, 2019, Robinson joined [[Wigan Athletic]] on a permanent three-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|title=Return of the Jedi – Wigan Athletic Complete Signing of USMNT International Antonee Robinson from Everton|url=https://www.wiganathletic.com/news/2019/july/return-of-the-jedi--wigan-athletic-complete-signing-of-usmnt-international-antonee-robinson-from-everton/|publisher=Wigan Athletic|date=July 15, 2019|access-date=July 15, 2019}}</ref> He made his debut for Wigan against [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]] and scored his first goal for the club in a 2–2 draw at [[Millwall F.C.|Millwall]] on November 26, 2019.<ref>{{cite news|title=Millwall 2 – 2 Wigan Athletic|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50469233|work=BBC Sport|date=November 26, 2019|access-date=November 27, 2019}}</ref>

After impressing for Wigan in the [[EFL Championship]] as one of the league's top left backs, Robinson was set to sign with [[Serie A]] side [[AC Milan]] for [[USD|US]]$13 million before the transfer deadline of January 31, 2020.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Report: AC Milan to Sign USMNT's Antonee Robinson From Wigan|url=https://www.si.com/football/2020/01/30/antonee-robinson-ac-milan-wigan-usmnt-transfer|magazine=Sports Illustrated|date=January 30, 2020|access-date=March 19, 2020}}</ref> However, the deal fell through when Robinson's medical examination at Milan revealed a heart rhythm irregularity for which further testing could not be completed before the deadline, and for which he would undergo an [[Ablation#Medicine|ablation]] procedure as treatment.<ref>{{cite news|title=Statement On Behalf Of Antonee Robinson|url=https://wiganathletic.com/news/2020/march/Statement-On-Behalf-of-Antonee-Robinson/|work=Wigan Athletic|date=March 12, 2020|access-date=March 19, 2020}}</ref>

===Fulham===
Following Wigan's relegation from the Championship, Robinson moved to Premier League club Fulham on August 20, 2020, for £2 million.<ref name=":0">{{cite news|title=Robinson Signs|url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2020/august/20/antonee-robinson-signs|work=Fulham FC|date=August 20, 2020|access-date=August 20, 2020}}</ref>

====2020–23: Development====
He made his debut for the club in a league cup game against Ipswich Town on September 16, 2020, in a Fulham win. He then played in the next round on September 23 against [[Sheffield Wednesday F.C.|Sheffield Wednesday]] in a 2–0 win. He played in the 3–0 loss to [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]] in the league cup on October 1. He made his Premier League debut on October 4, 2020, against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton]].

He scored his first goal for the club in an [[EFL Cup]] tie against [[Birmingham City]] on August 24, 2021.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Birmingham 0–2 Fulham|language=en-GB|work=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58239544|access-date=August 25, 2021}}</ref> Robinson was instrumental of Fulham winning the [[2021–22 EFL Championship|2021–22 Championship]] and its promotion back to the Premier League, featuring in 36 league games and scoring 3 goals. He was included on the [[2021–22 EFL Championship#Annual|EFL Championship Team of the Season]].<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":5" />

====2023–24: Fulham Player of the Season====
In July 2023, he signed a new contract with Fulham until 2028.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66139981|title=Fulham's Robinson signs new contract until 2028|work=BBC Sport }}</ref>

On December 3, 2023, Robinson made 13 interceptions in the 3–4 defeat to [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]], the most in a Premier League match since 2009 and was widely praised for his performances.<ref>{{Cite web |title=🧠 Antonee Robinson made 13 interceptions for Fulham at Liverpool today; no player has made more in a Premier League match since we started collecting Opta data from 2009/10 |url=https://twitter.com/WhoScored/status/1731344514336321704?s=20 |access-date=December 4, 2023 |website=X (formerly Twitter) |language=en}}</ref> In the same game, he became the first American to record 3 consecutive assists in the Premier League.<ref>{{Cite web |date=December 3, 2023 |title=Jedi is flying! USMNT star Antonee Robinson reaches Premier League assist milestone – not touched in 17 years – after setting up opening Fulham strike in Liverpool thriller {{!}} Goal.com India |url=https://www.goal.com/en-in/lists/jedi-usmnt-antonee-robinson-premier-league-assist-milestone-fulham-liverpool/blt396e9d896248132f |access-date=December 4, 2023 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-IN}}</ref> On December 20 in the [[2023–24 EFL Cup]] quarter-final against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]], Robinson forced an own-goal to get his side up 1–0 in the eventual 1–1 (7–6 penalties) win, helping his club to its first ever EFL semi-final appearance.<ref>{{Cite web |date=December 19, 2023 |title=Full-time: Everton 1–1 Fulham (Fulham win 7–6 on penalties) |url=https://ca.sports.yahoo.com/news/full-time-everton-1-1-221857191.html |access-date=December 20, 2023 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-CA}}</ref>

Robinson was awarded the [[2023–24 Fulham F.C. season|2023–24]] Fulham Player of the Season award.<ref name=":2" /> Considered as one of the Premier League's best left-backs of the season,<ref name=":6" /> he finished the [[2023–24 Premier League|2023–24 season]] with 37 league appearances and as the player with most interceptions in the Premier League in 81 occasions, 15 more than the second highest.<ref>{{cite web |title=Highest Interceptions by a player in the premier league this season |url=https://www.statmuse.com/fc/ask/highest-interceptions-in-the-premier-league |access-date=May 23, 2024 |publisher=StatMuse}}</ref><ref name=":2" /><ref name=":3" />

====2024–25====
On August 24, 2024, he assisted [[Alex Iwobi]] in the 2–1 win over [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]]. During the following match on August 31, he assisted [[Adama Traoré (footballer, born 1996)|Adama Traoré]] in the 1–1 draw against [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]]. On November 4, 2024, he assisted [[Harry Wilson (footballer, born 1997)|Harry Wilson]] in the 2–1 win over [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=August 31, 2024 |title=VIDEO: USMNT star Antonee Robinson provides second assist of Premier League season in Fulham's {{!}} Goal.com |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/usmnt-star-antonee-robinson-second-premier-league-assist-fulham/bltb7815b6bb34bc7f7 |access-date=August 31, 2024 |website=www.goal.com |language=en}}</ref> On December 14, Robinson recorded two assists in the 2–2 draw against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]], which accounted for his fifth and sixth assists of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |title=USMNT star Antonee Robinson assists twice in Fulham's 2–2 draw with Liverpool |url=https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/usmnt-star-antonee-robinson-assists-twice-fulhams-2-2-draw-liverpool |access-date=December 15, 2024 |website=FOX Sports |language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=":7" /> On December 29 against [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] he recorded his seventh assist, making him the third-highest assist leader of the [[2024–25 Premier League]] at the year's end.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Most Assists – Premier League Player Stats |url=https://www.premierleague.com/stats/top/players/goal_assist |access-date=December 27, 2024 |website=www.premierleague.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Antonee Robinson leads Premier League defenders with record-breaking assists – News – Nogomania |url=https://en.nogomania.com/read/Antonee-Robinson-leads-Premier-League-defenders-with-record-breaking-assists |access-date=December 31, 2024 |website=en.nogomania.com |language=en}}</ref> On January 14, 2025, he assisted both of Fulham's goals in the 2–3 defeat to [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=FC |first=Fulham |date=January 14, 2025 |title=West Ham 3–2 Fulham |url=https://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2025/january/14/west-ham-3-2-fulham/ |access-date=January 16, 2025 |website=Fulham FC}}</ref> He earned his tenth assist of the season in the 2–1 victory over [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] on February 1, only behind forward [[Mohamed Salah]] for the most in the league.<ref>{{Cite web |title=USMNT Rewind: Robinson reaches double-digit assists in England, Pulisic named Milan's January MVP, and more |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2025/02/usmnt-rewind-robinson-reaches-double-digit-assists-in-england-pulisic-named-milans-january-mvp |access-date=February 6, 2025 |website=www.ussoccer.com |language=en}}</ref>

On March 2, he captained Fulham and scored the winning [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]] (4–3) to eliminate [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in the [[2024–25 FA Cup]] Fifth round, advancing to the quarter-finals.<ref>{{Cite web |date=March 2, 2025 |title=Robinson, Fulham eliminate Manchester United from FA Cup – SBI Soccer |url=https://sbisoccer.com/2025/03/robinson-fulham-eliminate-manchester-united-from-fa-cup |access-date=March 3, 2025 |website=sbisoccer.com |language=en-US}}</ref>

He registered 10 assists in the Premier League that season, the most of any defender.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Antonee Robinson – Fulham Defender |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/player/_/id/222396/antonee-robinson |access-date=June 4, 2025 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File: Antonee Robinson WC2022 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|with the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]]]]
Robinson was eligible for both [[England national football team|England]] and the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]]. He was born in [[Milton Keynes]] and raised in [[Liverpool]], England. His father was born in England but raised in [[White Plains, New York]], and gained American citizenship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://americansoccernow.com/articles/antonee-robinson-making-most-of-loan-to-bolton|title=Antonee Robinson Making Most of Loan to Bolton|publisher=American Soccer Now|access-date=November 26, 2017}}</ref> Robinson is also of Jamaican descent through his paternal grandparents.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2020/09/07/antonee-robinson-fulham-wigan-milan-heart-usmnt-berhalter|title=Amid a Tumultuous Year, it All Works Out for Antonee Robinson|first=Brian|last=Straus|magazine=Sports Illustrated|date=September 7, 2020 }}</ref>

Robinson was first [[Cap (sport)|capped]] at under-18 level with the United States.<ref>{{cite web|title=U.S. U-18 MNT Falls To Germany 3–2 In Marbella, Spain|url=http://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2014/12/19/14/22/141219-u18mnt-falls-to-germany-in-spain|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141225202324/http://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2014/12/19/14/22/141219-u18mnt-falls-to-germany-in-spain|archive-date=December 25, 2014|access-date=August 10, 2017|publisher=U.S. Soccer}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://lionofviennasuite.sbnation.com/2017/8/4/16095540/done-deal-bolton-wanderers-complete-loan-signing-of-everton-defender-usa-efl-epl|title=Done Deal: Bolton Wanderers complete loan signing of Everton defender|date=August 4, 2017 |publisher=SB Nation|access-date=August 10, 2017}}</ref> He was also called into the United States under-20 side, although was not capped.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hitc.com/en-gb/2017/03/29/report-everton-take-jurgen-klinsmanns-son-jonathan-on-trial/|title=Report: Everton take Jurgen Klinsmann's son, Jonathan, on trial as Antonee Robinson attracts interest|date=March 29, 2017 |publisher=HITC|access-date=August 10, 2017}}</ref> In March 2018, Robinson was invited to both the United States senior and [[England national under-21 football team|England under-21]] camps, and accepted the United States senior call for a friendly against [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]] in which he was named to the bench.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/england-born-robinson-is-fully-committed-to-usmnt-and-looks-like-/dfinmw1ycr71mp5se7h95zkt|title=England-born Robinson is fully committed to USMNT, and looks like left back of the future|publisher=Goal.com|access-date=January 29, 2020}}</ref> He made his United States senior debut on May 28, 2018, playing the full 90 minutes in a 3–0 friendly win against Bolivia and recording an assist.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/club/united-states/660/blog/post/3511977/antonee-robinson-excels-in-us-debut-as-americans-breeze-past-bolivia|title=Antonee Robinson excels in U.S. debut as Americans breeze past Bolivia|date=May 29, 2018 |work=ESPN|access-date=May 29, 2018}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Nicknamed [[Jedi]], Robinson is known for his pace, work rate, and offensive ability.<ref>{{cite web |date=January 28, 2022 |title=Antonee 'Jedi' Robinson gives Berhalter, USMNT the World Cup qualifying win they were looking for |url=https://www.espn.com/Football/united-states-usa/story/4580735/antonee-jedi-robinson-gives-berhalterusmnt-the-world-cup-qualifying-win-they-were-looking-for |access-date=May 4, 2022 |website=ESPN}}{{Dead link|date=October 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=August 12, 2018 |title=Getting To Know: Antonee Robinson |url=https://wiganathletic.com/news/2018/august/getting-to-know-antonee-robinson/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180812194559/https://www.wiganathletic.com/news/2018/august/getting-to-know-antonee-robinson/ |archive-date=August 12, 2018 |access-date=May 4, 2022 |publisher=Wigan Athletic F.C.}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Robinson is engaged to Darcy Myers, and the couple has two children.<ref>{{Cite web |date=December 4, 2022 |title=Antonee Robinson's fiancée's tribute after USMNT's World Cup loss |url=https://nypost.com/2022/12/04/antonee-robinsons-fiancees-tribute-after-usmnts-world-cup-loss/ |access-date=September 14, 2025 |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=M |first=Krishna Prasad |date=June 23, 2024 |title=Who Is Antonee Robinson's Girlfriend? Meet USMNT Star's Fiance Darcy Myers and Discover About Their Children |url=https://www.essentiallysports.com/soccer-football-news-who-is-antonee-robinsons-girlfriend-meet-usmnt-stars-fiancee-darcy-myers-and-discover-about-their-children/ |access-date=September 14, 2025 |website=EssentiallySports |language=en}}</ref>

Robinson has used the nickname “Jedi” from early childhood as a reference to his love for the [[Star Wars]] franchise.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Antonee Robinson {{!}} USMNT {{!}} U.S. Soccer Official Site |url=https://ussoccer.com/players/r/antonee-robinson |access-date=2026-06-06 |website=ussoccer.com |language=en}}</ref>

